Inflation Explained: The Great Inflation of the 1970s explores one of the most significant economic events of the 20th century - the Great Inflation of the 1970s. This period of high inflation had a profound impact on the global economy, and its effects are still felt today. So, what exactly is inflation, and how did it get so out of control in the great inflation era from the 1970s to the 1980s? The great inflation is explained. What were the causes and consequences of this inflationary era? Examine the economic measures that were implemented to combat it. From the Nixon shock to the Volcker shock, we'll explore the major events that defined this tumultuous period in economic history. By understanding the Great Inflation of the 1970s, we can gain valuable insights into the nature of inflation and deflation and how to navigate these complex economic phenomena. So, if you're interested in learning more about the great inflation of the 1970s, then this video is for you.
